It&#x27;s all about reverse-engineering stuff; my usual workflow looks like:  
(1) Complile some Swift program & look at the disasembler listing of it (I use IDA and — for Objective-C — Hopper Disassembler);  
(2) Do some changes in source code in the program, compile it again, and see diffs in disassembler listing;
that way I can see what is changed and how.<p>About the @asmname thing: you can easily dump every default Swift module using a REPL command:<p>repl> :print_module Swift<p>There you can find a lot of interesting language lexems and more, so all you have to do is to try using them in your code until you don&#x27;t figure it out ;)
